Price does usually make a return to the 150% profit line at some point, after which things really take off.

Is the #Bitcoin bull market here?

Let's be crystal clear on this.

If you're thinking about new ATHs next, price discovery, and absolute euphoria inbound, then no... not quite.

That is reserved for Red Year, scheduled to begin after November 28th, 2024.

But if you mean the ramp-up to that then you're in luck, because that's where we are.

Blue Year gets us ready for the new ATHs. Every example has had a good performance, and price is on the brink of making new ATHs by the end of the year.

The cycles have so far been set in stone, structured and unwavering, centered around the date of the first halving, November 28th, 2012.

Greed is starting to creep into the market, do not be led astray as many were last cycle.

Still on track for a cycle top +/- 21 days from November 28th, 2025. My expected price is between 90 - 130k with most data pointing to 130k.

cleaned_data.original_text:
#Bitcoin is one of the most valuable assets the world has ever known and it has achieved this great status while being only a baby. On January 3, Bitcoin will be only 15 years old. As far as assets go, this is extraordinarily young.

So how valuable is the entire #Bitcoin network today? Well, as of this writing it stands at a value of $824 billion, and that's after a 4.5% decline over the last 24 hours. 

We as humans have a very hard time wrapping our minds around big numbers and with exponential numbers, which Bitcoin is good at producing, we are even worse. However, let's try to put into context how huge $824 billion really is. 

If you spent $1,000,000 dollars every single day from the time Christ was born (4 BC) to today, December 11, 2023, you still wouldn't be close to approaching $824 billion. ü§Ø These numbers are adjusted for inflation of course, but it shows the enormity of the value that is inside the Bitcoin network.

What's just as interesting is that this value is truly liquid in nature. It's not like the value locked in a home or a piece of property that must be sold over a multi-month process, if it can be sold at all. It's like fully operational, liquid cash that's available 24 hours a day, 364 days a year, and it is never down or "sick-at-sea." 

Additionally, this value in the Bitcoin network can be looked at and verified as existing by every human being on Earth. This value is audited every 10 minutes on average and these audits are available for the world to see. 

This value is infinitely divisible. It's instantly transportable to any location on the planet. It  can never be taken, confiscated, diluted or debased. It can't be touched or ruined by any human being. 

#Bitcoin's value in the network is cryptographically secure, has never been hacked, never will be hacked and it's growing faster than anything mankind has ever known.

Image 1 is the Bitcoin Network itself. 
Image 2 is the Bitcoin value.

And to think, the intellectually challenged still believe something like this is suddenly going to reverse and go to zero. Nothing this good, nothing this powerful, nothing this valuable can ever go to zero. In fact the only thing it can do is become more valuable. 

If I were you, I'd get some, just in case it really starts to catch on. #stackharder.

Bitcoin returns the power to the individual, 

In every way shape or form, 

Breaking the cycle of distraction and oppression,

Sadly,  

We live in a world driven by distractions and manipulations, 

Engineered to divert attention from the masses.

Governments keep the masses distracted with the proverbial "circuses"

Be it in the form of entertainment, sensationalist news, or even social welfare programs that are merely band-aids on a gaping wound.

The current financial system embodies this Orwellian paradigm.

When central authorities have the power to print money at will, manipulate interest rates, and monitor every transaction you make, 

This is not freedom; it's a gilded cage, built on a foundation of public ignorance and complacency.

Bitcoin the escape hatch from this Orwellian financial system. 

It offers the only path to true financial sovereignty, breaking us free from the Orwellian dystopias that central banks and fiat currencies have nudged us toward. 

So yes, if governments cannot or will not offer their citizens the stability and freedom they deserve, 

Then the people should turn to solutions that can. 

Bitcoin isn't just a choice; it's a necessity.

cleaned_data.cleaned_text: breaking :police_car_light: bitcoin traditing above $44,000. :fire: bitcoin bullrun has started let's gooooooo

super rough edges still, but this morning, we had the very first end-to-end universal money address (uma) transactions between different countries, wallets, and currencies powered by bitcoin lightning network under the hood : 1) in terminal mode from the us with in us dollars (with the wrong fee) to in ghana in ghanaian cedi (client-side receive not complete yet, so not shown, but received server-side, performance not optimized yet); 2) from argentina with in usdc to in the philippines in philippines peso; 3) from ghana with in btc (perf not optimized yet) to in the philippines in philippines peso. for all but one of these transactions, consumers will never need to know bitcoin was the net settlement asset and network between these institutions, just like sending an email doesn't require consumers to know anything about smtp. open-sourced and announced uma less than two months ago, so we're still in the very early phase of the standard roll-out. but, by the time these implementations get into the hands of consumers, the experience will be magical. an always-on, currency-agnostic, 24/7 settlement network with human-readable addresses. we wanted to share the same day even though much more work will happen to make this production ready in weeks to come. we're incredibly grateful to all our partners across the world and the ones actively implementing now. we really can't wait to make this mass market in 2024!

BitTime shows us clearly that we are following a cycle more like cycle 2 (2015 - 2018).

It proved this when #Bitcoin made its first early top (yellow dot) in July, and bottomed in August just like 2015 did.

Because of this, I think it makes perfect sense to end our first Blue Year rally in December, while most are waiting for January and ETF speculation.

The cycles told us this rise was coming before anyone was talking about ETFs, and in fact when most were advocating for a recession dump.

Not long ago I made the claim that I believed Bitcoin was topped at 45k, and I still stand by it.

The next scheduled sideways period is quickly approaching (small black horizontal arrow).

The 48k price target may be delayed until the second early top scheduled to come +/- 21 days from July 9th, 2024 (purple dot).

I firmly believe the power of the cycles will not be broken, even with potential ETFs on the horizon.

Greed surrounding #Bitcoin ETFs couldn't be higher, and data couldn't look more overheated.

This is why I have remained a step ahead, and have been saying that Bitcoin has found its local high at 45k.

The SMI has completely peaked, the first time this happens in every cycle has marked the cycle mid-top.

Analysts abroad are looking for the common .618 cycle retrace at 48k, meanwhile, when measuring from the April 2021 technical top, we're already there!

The major importance of this?

Better buying prices for those that need them. I believe around the 30k region.

I have been bullish since 25k when most were expecting 21 - 23k.

Data now says that it's time for a pause!

I don't think this time is any different.

The largest pools of capital on earth will soon be entering the #bitcoin market with massive buy orders based on retail demand for their ETF products. 

These firms have $30 trillion under management/advisory. Selling Bitcoin will be easy because the stage is set üëá

The 60/40 portfolio is dead. 30YR treasury bonds are down 50% since 2020. Smart money is starting to understand that the financial system is a sham. A lot of that money is on the sidelines wanting to flow into Bitcoin. Uncle Larry will normalize the inclusion of BTC in a standard portfolio allocation. 

Bitcoiners understand the nature of money and economics better than any other group of people, including the thousands of PhDs who work at the Federal Reserve. They have all drunk the cool-aid and they actually believe in the Keynesian system. But we understand that fiat is a scam, and we have no intention of giving up the hardest asset in the world in exchange for it. 

Point is, there's a wall of money about to flow into Bitcoin, and there aren't gonna be a lot of sellers. Yes, miners will be forced to sell some #BTC in order to cover electricity costs. But I suspect that most other people are going to hodl. There will be an army of hodlers, hundreds of millions strong, all around the world, peacefully rejecting tyranny and doing their part to restore sovereignty to the people. 

On the demand side, there are going to be an estimated $10 billion dollars per month of new demand entering the market, and hardly anyone on the ask. 

And while a sophisticated hedge fund might be able to cleverly and patiently leg into a #Bitcoin position opportunistically, these firms are going to have to buy spot #BTC as retail investors remit cash for ETF shares. If $1 billion comes in on a random Tuesday, the firm has to turn around and buy spot #BTC, even if there are hardly any sellers. Even if their buy order pushes up the price by $10k on a single hourly candle. 

No one is ready for this.

In fact, no 2-week RVI has reached this high ever outside of the context of a cycle top, or ramp-up to it.

So what does this mean? Are we ramping up to a new ATH?

Not so fast.

We have never seen a move this powerful come in the middle of the cycle.

This time is not different different, I must continue to say it because so many people believe it is.

We knew this was coming, long-term data said so.

What you are seeing here is the product of 8 months of sideways price action that we had in 2023.

The momentum was built, and now the spring is released.

There are hard stops in the near future between 47 and 49k.

Many fell into the recession fears at 25k, so many were
confident we would return to the lows at 15.5k, or at least 21 - 23k.

Mass psychology lives on repeat

cleaned_data.original_text:
Has #Bitcoin finished this rally?

Let's talk liquidity moves

Last 2 complete moves to downside and then upside for the S&P tell a story of how liquidity flows to Bitcoin and crypto, after being the first mover.

2019 SPX moves to new ATH with 28% gain, BTC does a 352% in the same period, lagging. 

So the multiplier is 12x

Again, after pandemic, SPX does a 118% return, and BTC 1800% - multiplier is 15x

Now we had '22 bottom, and SPX again moves first, with little room to reach old ATH, which does a 37% return (I'm 99% certain we'll do a new SPX ATH soon)

If we apply a 12x multiplier from this lagging SPX move to BTC, well, the math says it all.

I looked through different lenses since January '23 for why BTC would NOT reach a new ATH before halving, and I couldn't find any.

Let's see how history is written next 6 months.

I regularly discuss how #Bitcoin is a tool to ‚Äúbank the unbanked‚Äù. 

Unfortunately, the recognition of #Bitcoin's role as a significant catalyst for enhancing the human condition is still not widely acknowledged or understood. This innovative digital currency represents more than just a financial tool; it embodies a paradigm shift in how we perceive and interact with the global economy while providing opportunities for economic mobility to the least advantaged.

One of the most critical challenges in our world today is the lack of access to reliable and inclusive financial services. Billions of people across the globe (including in the USA) find themselves hindered by the absence of basic banking facilities, access to digital currency, and secure methods to store and grow their wealth. This systemic exclusion from the financial mainstream has been a significant barrier to improving their quality of life, leaving them vulnerable and often unable to participate in the global economy effectively.

#Bitcoin steps in as a potential solution to this pervasive issue. It democratizes financial services, offering a decentralized platform that is not controlled by any single entity, government, or organization. This characteristic of #Bitcoin ensures that it remains neutral and accessible to everyone, irrespective of their geographical location, social status, or cultural background.

Moreover, #Bitcoin transcends traditional barriers such as sex, gender, race, sexuality, political affiliation, national origin, and religion. Its architecture ensures that anyone with internet access can participate in the global economy, providing a level playing field for all. This inclusivity is a significant departure from traditional financial systems, which often allow discriminatory practices to take place or impose barriers which prevent equal access. 

Additionally, #Bitcoin offers an alternative to unstable local currencies and financial systems. In regions where inflation runs rampant or where national currencies are devalued, #Bitcoin presents a more stable store of value, helping individuals preserve their wealth in a more secure form which can‚Äôt be readily taken from them by corrupt actors. 

#Bitcoin is not just a digital currency; it's a tool for social and economic empowerment. It promises a future where financial inclusion is not just a privilege for the affluent but a fundamental right accessible to all, paving the way for a more equitable and prosperous global society.

Many still haven‚Äôt learned about how #Bitcoin can and will ‚Äúbank the unbanked‚Äù, but I believe the next decade will be remembered as a time when this feature of #Bitcoin shines brightly. 

Slowly, then suddenly.

#Bitcoin will become money in stages.

Stage 1: Bitcoin is used store of value.

Stage 2: Bitcoin becomes a widely accepted medium of exchange.

Stage 3: The value to goods and services is assigned in terms of Bitcoin.

#Bitcoin‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ is somewhere between stage 1 and stage 2.

As more people see how well it portrays the characteristics of a store of value (durable, scarce), they start accumulating it to save for the future.

Eventually, the people who want to hold it as a store of value also want to start accepting it in exchange for goods and services. They create and sell some form of value, whether it's their time or an actual good.

At this point, the people who have held their Bitcoin for a while are willing to part with their coins which have significantly appreciated in terms of purchasing power. To be a medium of exchange, money has to be portable and divisible.

This is where Bitcoin is today! More companies are saying they want to accept #BTC‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ in exchange for their product offerings.

When enough merchants accept Bitcoin for their goods and services, customers may start asking for prices in terms of Bitcoin. In this case, fungibility and salability play a role.

We are still very early when it comes to #Bitcoin‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ, but most average people think we should be a lot further along. How is that possible when 99% of the world doesn't get how money works?

It takes longer than a few years for a form of money to be widely accepted. Today, the only thing holding Bitcoin back is the willingness of people to learn about it.

It took gold 2,000 years to move from being a store of value to a medium of exchange. Bitcoin's adoption has been much faster due to the internet. It's only taken 15 years for Bitcoin to almost reach the same stage as gold in its progression.

We're a while away from Bitcoin being used as a unit of account, but progress happens slowly and then suddenly. Every 4 years more people see Bitcoin as something that will never go away.

With the speed at which we are progressing, Bitcoin could be a world reserve asset within 20 years!

Demystifying Crypto's Movements: Unveiling the Link Between #Bitcoin and Global Liquidity

In the ever-evolving world of cryptocurrency, understanding the underlying factors driving price movements is crucial for making informed investment decisions. While technical analysis and fundamental factors play a role, a key driver often overlooked is the influence of global liquidity cycles.

Understanding Global Liquidity Cycles

Global liquidity cycles refer to the recurring periods of expansion and contraction in the overall availability of capital. These cycles are largely influenced by central bank policies, such as interest rates and quantitative easing measures.

Bitcoin's Sensitivity to Global Liquidity

Bitcoin, as the flagship cryptocurrency, has demonstrated a strong correlation with global liquidity cycles. During periods of expansion, increased liquidity flows into riskier assets, such as cryptocurrencies, leading to upward price movements for Bitcoin and other altcoins.

The Ripple Effect: #Altcoins Follow Bitcoin's Lead

This correlation extends beyond Bitcoin to the broader cryptocurrency market. Altcoins, or alternative cryptocurrencies, often mirror Bitcoin's price movements, reflecting the underlying sentiment and investor behavior in the crypto space.

Implications for Crypto Investors

For crypto investors, understanding the connection between Bitcoin and global liquidity is essential for navigating market fluctuations and making strategic investment decisions. By recognizing the influence of these cycles, investors can position themselves to capitalize on periods of increased liquidity and avoid potential risks during contractions.

Conclusion

In the dynamic realm of cryptocurrency, global liquidity cycles play a significant role in shaping price movements. Bitcoin, as the market's bellwether, serves as a leading indicator for the broader cryptocurrency space. By recognizing this connection, investors can enhance their understanding of market dynamics and make informed decisions to navigate the crypto landscape with greater confidence.
